## Metadata Requirements

### Required Metadata for Every Archived Dataset

| Field | Description | Example |
|-------|-------------|---------|
| Title | Human-readable name | "MNIST digit recognition dataset v2" |
| Description | What the data contains and how it was collected | 500 words max |
| Creator | Who created or collected the data | "Lab Name, PI Name" |
| Date created | When data was collected or generated | ISO 8601: 2026-02-15 |
| Version | Dataset version identifier | "v2.1" |
| License | Usage rights | "CC BY 4.0" |
| Format | File format(s) | "Parquet, PNG" |
| Size | Total storage size | "15 GB" |
| Hash | Content integrity hash | SHA-256 of archive |
| Schema | Column names, types, units | Embedded or sidecar file |
| Provenance | How data was derived | "Collected from X, processed by Y" |
| Related publications | Papers using this data | DOI list |

### Metadata File Format

```yaml
# dataset_metadata.yaml -- co-located with data
title: "Experiment 42 Results"
description: "Training and evaluation results for attention mechanism comparison"
creator: "Research Team"
date_created: "2026-02-15"
version: "1.0"
license: "CC BY 4.0"
format: "Parquet"
size_bytes: 1073741824
sha256: "abc123..."
schema:
  - name: "epoch"
    type: "int"
    description: "Training epoch number"
  - name: "loss"
    type: "float64"
    description: "Cross-entropy loss"
    unit: "nats"
provenance:
  source_code: "https://github.com/org/repo, commit abc123"
  source_data: "doi:10.xxxx/yyyy"
  processing_steps:
    - "Raw logs parsed by scripts/parse_logs.py"
    - "Outlier runs excluded per pre-registered criteria"
```

